               <msContents>
                 <summary>Copy of a receipt for 15 art. of wheat received by the mesites Demetrios through his agent Theogiton from Nilion, the assistant (?) of the sitologoi in Tebtynis.  The grain was from the cleruchic and "requisitioned" (i.e., frumentum emptum) accounts.</summary>
                 <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; back blank</note>
                     <note type="general">15 lines; broken at bottom. </note>
                     <note type="general">The hand is clear, shows the constitutive strokes of a letter, and slopes to the right</note>
                     <note type="general">Space of 2.5 cm between lines 10 and 11</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                 </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
